{"id":6113,"date":"2024-02-26T17:21:02","date_gmt":"2020-02-26T11:51:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=6113"},"modified":"2023-04-15T15:20:20","modified_gmt":"2023-04-15T09:50:20","slug":"quartz-countertops","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/quartz-countertops\/","title":{"rendered":"Kitchen Quartz Countertops For Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Quartz kitchen countertops are your best bet if you are looking at a kitchen remodel<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A kitchen is only as good as the countertop. True, that. The countertop is the most used element in the kitchen and so you would do well to invest in a durable as well as good-looking one. Quartz kitchen countertops are, for sure, your best bet.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Fun Fact:<\/strong> Quartz countertops may or may not actually have that much quartz in them!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Quartz countertops are not solid slabs of quartz mineral, as the name suggests, but are an engineered stone product. They are composed of pulverised stone-like materials and minerals combined with polymer resins for hardness and binding. One of the latest and best man-made kitchen countertop materials, these worktops have gained popularity due to their durability and yet natural stone-like beauty.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read on to find out more about quartz kitchen countertops and why you should definitely consider them if you are looking at a kitchen remodel.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Kitchen cabinet design to glam up your interiors\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17142806\/kitchen-cabinet-design-to-glam-up-your-interiors.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Quartz Countertops Come In An Endless Variety Of Colours And Styles<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The inclusion of quartz crystals, waste marble, granite and other natural minerals gives quartz countertops an organic texture that can compete with any natural stone in look and feel. Since they are engineered slabs, quartz countertops are available in a variety of different colours and styles. They can also be custom-fabricated in any size and shape.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010306\/types-of-quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz kitchen countertops with granite and other natural minerals\" class=\"wp-image-6125\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010306\/types-of-quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010306\/types-of-quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010306\/types-of-quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010306\/types-of-quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Pigmentation is used to give quartz countertops different colours<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Some quartz countertops look just like marble complete with convincing veining. White engineered quartz countertops with black or bluish veins can easily be mistaken for natural marble.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010247\/quartz-countertops-cost-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\" Quartz countertops cost for you that fits under your budget\" class=\"wp-image-6120\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010247\/quartz-countertops-cost-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010247\/quartz-countertops-cost-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010247\/quartz-countertops-cost-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010247\/quartz-countertops-cost-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Give your kitchen the luxurious look and feel of marble without breaking the bank<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Common colours for stone-look countertops are white, black, brown and grey. This gorgeous brown quartz counter looks absolutely stunning in a white distressed finished retro kitchen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010250\/quartz-countertops-price-for-you.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz countertops price in your budget where gorgeous brown quartz counter looks absolutely stunning\" class=\"wp-image-6121\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010250\/quartz-countertops-price-for-you.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010250\/quartz-countertops-price-for-you-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010250\/quartz-countertops-price-for-you-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010250\/quartz-countertops-price-for-you-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>The deep texture of the quartz worktop is rustic and natural-looking<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This cold steel grey quartz countertop is sleek and provides a beautiful contrast to the wood laminate cabinets in this modern kitchen. With an engineered slab, there\u2019s no need to worry about cooking spills and staining!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010239\/black-quartz-countertops-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"Black quartz countertops which are sleek and provides a beautiful contrast to the wood laminate cabinet\" class=\"wp-image-6118\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010239\/black-quartz-countertops-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010239\/black-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010239\/black-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010239\/black-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Grey and brown make for a beautiful pairing in the kitchen<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This absolutely stunning slab has so many colours in it that it could easily pass off as natural stone. The varying shades of black, brown and white give the quartz countertop an organic depth and visual appeal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Cool kitchen design hacks on a budget\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/17140431\/cool-kitchen-design-hacks-on-budget.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010301\/quartz-stone-countertop-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz stone countertop where various shades of black, brown and white give the quartz countertop an organic depth\" class=\"wp-image-6124\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010301\/quartz-stone-countertop-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010301\/quartz-stone-countertop-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010301\/quartz-stone-countertop-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010301\/quartz-stone-countertop-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>This striking deep brown quartz countertop steals the show without a doubt!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In varying hues of brown and beige, the countertop and artistically laid textured backsplash tiles, go hand in hand to give this kitchen a rustic and yet elegant edge.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010254\/quartz-countertops-that-look-like-marble.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz countertops that look like marble with artistically textured backsplash tiles\" class=\"wp-image-6122\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010254\/quartz-countertops-that-look-like-marble.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010254\/quartz-countertops-that-look-like-marble-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010254\/quartz-countertops-that-look-like-marble-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010254\/quartz-countertops-that-look-like-marble-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Choose a countertop that seamlessly integrates with the rest of your kitchen design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And you if still aren\u2019t convinced, here are some added reasons why you should be opting for a quartz kitchen countertop:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-backsplash-ideas\/\">Kitchen Backsplash Ideas For Your Home<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Durability<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Quartz countertops are extremely hard and non-porous and hence stain and scratch resistant. They make for practical worktops for a busy kitchen space which puts hygiene first. Several quartz kitchen counters even have antibacterial agents added to them. They are heat resistant too and are easy to maintain since they don\u2019t require an annual sealing unlike natural stone.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010235\/best-quartz-countertops-for-your-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"Best quartz countertops which are stain and scratch-resistant for your kitchen\" class=\"wp-image-6117\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010235\/best-quartz-countertops-for-your-kitchen.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010235\/best-quartz-countertops-for-your-kitchen-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010235\/best-quartz-countertops-for-your-kitchen-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010235\/best-quartz-countertops-for-your-kitchen-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Being extremely hard, quartz kitchen countertops are ideal for your cooking space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Uniformity<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Since they are engineered slabs, quartz countertops rarely have imperfections. Controlled manufacturing ensures uniformity in the slabs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010309\/white-quartz-countertops-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"White quartz countertops where manufacturing ensures uniformity in the slabs\" class=\"wp-image-6126\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010309\/white-quartz-countertops-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010309\/white-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010309\/white-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010309\/white-quartz-countertops-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>You won\u2019t have to deal with flaws and inclusions found in natural stone slabs<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Environmentally Friendly Quartz Countertops<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Quartz countertops are greener than other options. Around 90 percent of minerals used to form the base of a quartz countertop are waste-products of other quarrying or manufacturing processes. Even the resins used as binders in engineered quartz countertops are not so synthetic.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010258\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"Quartz kitchen countertops which are greener than other options\" class=\"wp-image-6123\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010258\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010258\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010258\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/21010258\/quartz-kitchen-countertops-for-your-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption>Practical, beautiful and eco-friendly \u2013 what more could you ask for?<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Budget friendly modern kitchen interior design\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/15145905\/budget-friendly-modern-kitchen-interior-design.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Cons<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The only thing that can be used against quartz countertops is that they don\u2019t come cheap (when compared to other man-made options) and would probably cost you as much as a natural granite slab. They are also exceedingly heavy in comparison to worktops in solid-surface material, ceramic tile or laminate, but then so are natural stone slabs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Bottom Line<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Quartz kitchen countertops are a no brainer. With their kind of versatility and practicality, it would be pointless to look at anything else. They offer the best of all worlds \u2013 combining the chaotic appearance of natural stone without its unpredictability. They have the flexibility of solid-surface material and yet are highly durable. And they lend a luxurious finish to the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/modular-kitchen-design\/\">Modular kitchen<\/a> that you can customise according to your aesthetic sensibility and style. What\u2019s there not to like? Quartz countertops for the win, we say!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/10-different-types-of-kitchen-countertops\/\">10 Different Types Of Kitchen Countertops<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/8-best-colour-combinations-for-kitchen\/\">8 Best Colour Combinations For Your Kitchen<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/price-of-modular-kitchen\/\">Factors That Affect The Price Of Your Modular Kitchen<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Modular Kitchens At Best Prices<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Speak to our kitchen experts today!<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>\n                    +91\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+44\"\n                    data-img